This paper is primarily focused on the training of generative adversarial networks (GANs), which is a topic within the field of machine learning. Specifically, it proposes a novel training method for GANs called Fictitious GAN. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, since GANs are often used in computer vision applications, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses game theory and convergence issues, which could place it in the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, since the paper is focused on deep neural networks, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category.
